stics of\nvertical mixing at these radii. Our modeled fluxes of observable molecules\nrespond sensitively to changes in the disk gas temperature, inner radius, and\nthe total elemental C/O ratio. As a result, mid-infrared observations of disks\nwill be useful probes of these fundamental disk parameters, including the C/O\nratio, which can be compared to values determined for planetary atmospheres.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Jan 2021 19:01:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-10"}
